author: Courtesy of SU Sports Information
title: SU soccer drops tough 2-1 contest to Gannon
text:
PHOTO BY BILL SLATTERY Gallucci 
Freshman forward Joey Gallucci challenges the Gannon keeper for the ball during the Raiders’ 2-1 loss. Posted: Tuesday, October 6, 2015 6:00 am SU soccer drops tough 2-1 contest to Gannon Courtesy of SU Sports Information ShipNC.com | 0 comments 
The Shippensburg University men’s soccer team suffered a tough loss to Gannon on Saturday, 2-1, in a pivotal Pennsylvania State Athletic Conference (PSAC) matchup on a rainy, windy and cold day at David See Field. 
Shippensburg (4-6, 1-5 PSAC) rallied from a 1-0 deficit to tie the score in the 60th minute as senior Derek Adams scored his third goal of the season by sliding a shot into the lower right portion of the goal off a brilliant feed from freshman Joey Gallucci. kAmv2??@?
